  "prompt": "Which Pakistani universities are recognized by Australian immigration department?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the Australian immigration authorities do not maintain a specific list of recognized foreign universities. Instead, qualifications from Pakistani institutions are typically evaluated by the Australian Department of Education, Skills and Employment, or relevant assessing authorities, to determine if they meet Australian standards. However, several Pakistani universities are generally well-regarded and could be more likely to meet these standards due to their accreditation and reputation. Some of these institutions include:\n\n1. **University of the Punjab**\n2. **Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS)**\n3. **National University of Sciences and Technology (NUST)**\n4. **University of Karachi**\n5. **Quaid-i-Azam University**\n6. **Aga Khan University**\n7. **Institute of Business Administration (IBA), Karachi**\n\nRecognition can depend on the specific course and level of study. It is advisable for prospective students or immigrants to have their credentials assessed by a relevant Australian body, such as the Australian Qualifications Framework (AQF) or a specific professional organization relevant to their field of study. Additionally, for the most up-to-date and specific guidance, consulting the official sources or a migration agent is recommended.",
